      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Mr. Charles White is a native of Buckingham County,
         Virginia. He has devoted much time and effort to document the
         history of African-Americans in the county of Buckingham.</p>
         <p>His research resulted in the publication of 
         <title render="italic">The Hidden and Forgotten</title>. Mr.
         White is a retired vocational education teacher and a graduate
         of Virginia State University.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of materials collected by Mr.
         Charles White while he was engaged in writing 
         <title render="italic">A History of Blacks in Buckingham
         County, Va</title>. There are copies of wills, letters, and
         news clippings. Also, included are original copies of the
         official journal of the Virginia Baptist Convention: 
         <title render="italic">The Expected</title>.</p>
         <p>
         <title render="italic">The Expected</title>contains material
         documenting the Virginia Baptist State Convention. Subjects
         covered include the women's museum department, the role of
         church and society, information about different chuches,
         Virginia Union University and sketches of different minutes in
         the convention.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Series Description</head>
         <p>Series I. Reserach Materials Copies of documents collected
         by Mr. White to support his research.</p>
         <p>Series II. Printed A. The Expected, The official organ of
         the Virginia Baptist Convention.</p>
      </arrangement>
